similar to writing songs, iâ€™ll sketch without much thought until something clicks. 

when iâ€™ve mapped out the picture in pencil iâ€™ll trace it with an inking tool, then color, then shading.

once iâ€™ve got a song i love completely stripped down i will send vocals to one of my producer homies (usually @iamtarro). 

he builds the music up around my vocal so everything is tailored to the song. and boom, weâ€™ve got a classic ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ³ğŸ¤Œ

i mix the song as i record it then pass it off to my engineer when itâ€™s final.

sometimes i feel like iâ€™m painting a picture with my adlibs and back up vocals/harmonies. the way those vocals are processed can change the whole feeling of a song.

i write to just guitar so i know the song holds up on its own. 

i almost never write anything down when im by myself. i just freestyle melodies on the mic and carve out sections i like. 

once iâ€™ve got a good hook iâ€™ll come up w lyrics in my head and plug them in as they hit me.

the way i create music always varies depending on where i am and who iâ€™m with. 

when iâ€™m in the room with others iâ€™ll write in my phone and sing out loud to include everyone.
